Horace takes his expression from the Greek proverb λάθε βιώσας, which ap- pears to have been used by the Epicureans and Cyrenaics. Plutarch opposes the rule in a treatise of which the title is εἷ καλῶς εἴρηται τὺ λάθε βιώσας. Erasmus quotes Ovid (Trist. iii. 4. 25) :—
